abstract: BALDWIN'S, L.I., Aug. 11. -- Burglars broke into two houses here yesterday and into one at Oceanside. The three robberies were committed in daylight, and while in each case the value of articles secured by the thieves was very light, they made up for it by destroying many articles too bulky to be carried off. All the families were absent at the time, and there is no clue to the burglars.

abstract: The people live much in public, and the poorer classes, instead of eating their meals at home, as is the manner of the unsociable Hindu, seem usually to breakfast and dine at one of the itinerant cookshops to be found at every street corner. abstract: PITTSBURG, Aug. 18 -- Neither the stock nor local money situation shows any very marked change this week. abstract: CHICAGO, Aug. 24. -- The morning call was the liveliest the Exchange has had for many weeks. The market was purely a speculative one and confined entirely to West Chicago. Opening at 126, it was sold as rapidly as bids were made on a declining scale downward until 123 1/8 was reached, a break of 3 1/8 from yesterday's weak close and 4 1/4 off from yesterday's opening.

abstract: PALATKA, Fla., Aug. 24. -- R.C. Scott. City Treasurer of Jacksonville, and Market Inspector McCurdy of that city are under arrest here charged with kidnapping B.W. Helverstor says that Scott and McCurdy, with two other men, took him in a closed carriage to a lonely spot outside of the city and gagged him.

abstract: BIRMINGHAM, Ala., Aug. 30. -- The Kolbo-Populo-Republico combine has made a change in its Congressional slate, adopted two days ago. This contest promises to be a hard-fought one, as the two teams have been keen rivals for some time. The New-Jerseys are confident of winning. Their followers believe that their team is stronger than Orange, and will go along willing to back their opinions heavily.
